-- Stocks in U.S. Extend Advance After Consumer Confidence Tops Forecasts
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2010-10-01T13:58:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/stocks-in-u-s-extend-advance-after-consumer-confidence-tops-forecasts.html
U.S. stocks extended gains after a
gauge of consumer confidence topped economists’ estimates.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index climbe 0.7 percent to
1,148.63 at 9:57 a.m. in New York. The Dow Jones Industrial
Average increased 66.38 points, or 0.6 percent, to 10,854.43  The Thomson Reuters/University of Michigan final index of
consumer sentiment came in at 68.2 for September, topping
economists’ forecasts for a reading of 67.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  